IT is all about finding love again for popular media personality, Toke Makinwa in 2022. The 37-year-old OAP recently released her wishlist for 2022 stressing that someone’s son must find her. “Somebody’s son must find me 22,” she captioned a video.   Rex Suru opens up on life, new songs and record label     OB plans big with Afro-Soul for 2022     AY comedian: I’m happy that people are supporting Nollywood   Toke had earlier dropped her wishes for the year. She wrote: “2022 is going to look a lot like; a whole lot of God, whole lot of money, a whole lot of peace, a whole lot of travellings, a whole lot of life-changing experiences, a whole lot of catching flights and feelings and a whole lot of sex.” - Advertisement - Makinwa who lost both her parents at a tender age married Maje Ayida on January 15, 2014. The marriage was dissolved by a Lagos High Court on the grounds that Ayida committed adultery in 2017.